<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text"><p>See for example <a href="http://crazedmuleproductions.blogspot.com/2005/12/using-ffmpeg-to-combine-audio-and.html">http://crazedmuleproductions.blogspot.com/2005/12/using-ffmpeg-to-combine-audio-and.html</a></p>

<p>So it should be something to the effect of:</p>

<pre><code>ffmpeg -i audio.wav -i video.mp4 -acodec copy -vcodec copy output.mp4
</code></pre>

<p>You might want to transcode the audio in some way, change <code>-acodec copy</code> to your desired audio codec.</p>
</div>
    <table class="fw">
    <tr>
