        <td class="comment-text"><div><span class="comment-copy">i don&#39;t think mp4 containers can have wav audio streams. Try <code>ffmpeg -i audio.wav -i video.mp4 -acodec copy -vcodec copy -f mkv output.mkv</code></span> &ndash;&nbsp;<a href="/users/161208/luke" title="641 reputation" class="comment-user">Luke</a> <span class="comment-date" dir="ltr"><span title="2013-03-12 23:29:28Z" class="relativetime-clean">Mar 12 at 23:29</span></span></div></td>
